.TH NEX 1 "2026-07-12" "nodex 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nodex \- open infrastructure management for self\-hosters
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nodex
[\fIGLOBAL\-FLAGS\fR]
\fICOMMAND\fR
[\fICOMMAND\-ARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nodex
is a unified command\-line interface for managing self\-hosted infrastructure.
It supports Proxmox VE with a provider\-based architecture that can be extended
to other platforms.
.SH GLOBAL FLAGS
.TP
.BI \-\-profile " " \fINAME\fR
Override the current profile.
.TP
.BI \-\-output " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format: \fBtable\fR, \fBjson\fR, or \fByaml\fR.
Default: table (TTY), json (non\-TTY).
.TP
.BI \-\-timeout " " \fIDURATION\fR
Request timeout (default: 30s).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable color output.
.TP
.B \-\-non\-interactive
Disable interactive prompts.
.TP
.B \-\-quiet
Suppress non\-essential output.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Info\-level stderr output.
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Debug\-level stderr output (redacted).
.SH COMMANDS
.SS nodex init
Initialize nodex configuration interactively.
.SS nodex profile add \fINAME\fR
Add a new connection profile.
.SS nodex profile list
List all configured profiles.
.SS nodex profile show \fINAME\fR
Show details for a specific profile.
.SS nodex profile use \fINAME\fR
Set the current active profile.
.SS nodex profile current
Show the current active profile.
.SS nodex profile test [\fINAME\fR]
Test connectivity for a profile.
.SS nodex profile remove \fINAME\fR
Remove a profile.
.SS nodex provider list
List available providers.
.SS nodex provider capabilities \fINAME\fR
Show capabilities for a provider.
.SS nodex node list
List all nodes.
.SS nodex vm list
List all virtual machines.
.SS nodex container list
List all containers.
.SS nodex storage list
List all storage pools.
.SS nodex doctor
Check system health and connectivity.
.SS nodex version
Print version information.
.SS nodex help [\fICOMMAND\fR]
Show help for a command.
.SH CREDENTIALS
Credentials are resolved in the following order:
.TP 1.
\fBcredential_ref\fR in profile (e.g., \fBkeyring:myprofile\fR, \fBfile:default\fR)
.TP 2.
Environment variables (e.g., \fBNODEX_PROFILE_TOKEN\fR)
.TP 3.
Credential files in \fI~/.nodex/credentials/\fR
.PP
Supported credential backends:
.TP
.B keyring
OS keyring (macOS Keychain, Linux Secret Service, Windows Credential Manager).
.TP
.B file
JSON files in \fI~/.nodex/credentials/\fR.
.TP
.B env
Environment variables.
.TP
.B stdin
Interactive prompt (read\-only, does not store).
.SH PROFILES
Profiles are stored in \fI~/.config/nodex/config.yaml\fR.
Each profile specifies a provider, endpoint, and optional credential reference.
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 2
Usage error
.TP
.B 3
Configuration error
.TP
.B 4
Credential unavailable
.TP
.B 5
Authentication failed
.TP
.B 6
Authorization denied
.TP
.B 7
Network error
.TP
.B 8
TLS error
.TP
.B 9
Incompatibility
.TP
.B 10
Unsupported capability
.TP
.B 11
Partial failure
.TP
.B 12
Provider error
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/nodex/config.yaml
Main configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.nodex/credentials/
Credential files directory.
.SH EXAMPLES
Add a Proxmox profile:
.PP
.RS
nodex profile add myserver
.RE
.PP
Set the endpoint:
.PP
.RS
nodex profile show myserver
.RE
.PP
Test connectivity:
.PP
.RS
nodex profile test myserver
.RE
.PP
List nodes:
.PP
.RS
nodex node list
.RE
.PP
Output as JSON:
.PP
.RS
nodex \-\-output json node list
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.BI NODEX_ " " \fIPROFILE\fR "_TOKEN"
API token for the given profile.
.TP
.BI NODEX_ " " \fIPROFILE\fR "_TOKEN_ID"
Token ID for the given profile.
.TP
.BI NODEX_ " " \fIPROFILE\fR "_TOKEN_SECRET"
Token secret for the given profile.
